  "body": "When keywords are misspelled in contracts, the error output is not very helpful for new users, i saw two cases of this being a problem in the truffle gitter today.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\nSomeone misspelled `pragma` as `pramga` and the resulting error message reads:\r\n\r\n`Error parsing /path/Contract.sol: Expected \"contract\", \"import\", \"interface\", \"library\", \"pragma\", \"using\", comment, end of input, end of line, or whitespace but \"p\" found`\r\n\r\nThe message would be a lot more helpful if it printed the whole word.",
